RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 60. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR REGISTERED INDIANA BREDS MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: INDY BIZ set the pace into the first turn while moving into the turn from the three path, widened through the backstretch, continued to widen when under minimal urging, extended the advantage through the lane while under minimal encouragement. SAN RONIN chased the winner from the outset while near the inside, continued closest to the top one in late turn, lost the place spot into the lane then stayed on to regain the runner-up spot through the final sixteenth. SEMINOLE AUSTIN was unhurried into the backstretch, bid into the far turn while three wide and in the four path, continued under a drive into the lane to get nearest the winner then tired and lost the place spot late. GRAY MIKE chased the pace from the three path into the far turn, was asked for more into the lane and tired. JACK THE BIRD never a factor while racing in mid-pack through the far turn. RUNNING SMART was steadied between rivals into the first turn, continued near the inside into the far turn, raced in the four path through the turn and steadily lost ground. BINNINGTON BLUES raced along the inside into the far turn, came off the inside in late turn and into the lane and was empty. QUALITY DANCER saved ground throughout and steadily faded. INEEDRELIEF was outrun while off the inside.

ENTRY.NAME: San Ronin
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased winner, no match, clear place

ENTRY.NAME: Gray Mike
ENTRY.OWNER: Clabar Mor Stables LLC and Haran Thoroughbreds LLC

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SIGNATURE STREET chased the pace from the inside through the turn and into the lane, came off the rail when straightening, caught the leader near the eighth pole and drove past. CIERRA EMPIRE raced along the inside through the turns, bid into the lane from the two path and was up for place spot. SHEZA NUT raced on a clear pace while near the inside, continued clear through late turn, was caught near the eighth pole, yielded to the winner and lost the place spot late while saving the show spot. AMERICANA ANNA saved ground through the turn, came into the lane from four or five path and showed late energy to be gaining to the wire. NORA'S STAR was in the two or three path through the turns, was asked for more approaching the quarter pole then weakened after straightening in the lane. TAP THE LINE raced three wide through the first turn, continued in the four path through the far turn and never was a factor. BICKERMENTS was unhurried while off the rail through the far turn, bid into the lane from the five path, was under a strong drive to inside the eighth pole and was suddenly done near the sixteenth pole.

LITTLE GRAY FLOWER in mid-pack while off the rail into the turn, moved through the three path through mid-turn, swung into the lane from the seven path and was up for the show spot. BIRDSOFAFEATHER bid four wide through the turn, came into the lane from the six path and was never a threat through the final eighth. ZIPSY ROSE LEE was well back while in the two path through the far turn, angled into the eight path for the drive then moved up while not a menace. MISS DIAMOND RICH was three wide through the first turn, continued off the inside through the turn, came into the lane from the five path and moved up. PRETTY HEART was in the two path into the far turn when never far back, asked into the lane and was empty. MALI BALI chased the pace along the inside through the turn and into the lane then retreated. ARRINGTON was never a factor while racing far back. EMERSON'S DREAM chased the pace from the three path into the far turn, bid three wide through the turn then folded up entering the lane. TEN LIL VICTORIES chased the pace from the three path into the turn, was two wide through the turn and retreated through the lane.
